doctype html
html(lang='en')
  head
    title FISH Clean Abort Explained
    style.
        dd {
            margin-left: 2em;
        }
  body
    h2 FISH CLEAN ABORT FEATURES
    p.
        The Clean Abort feature allows FISH to gracefully handle participants who take too long
        to read the rules or who wait too long in the lobby for the simulation to start.
        When enabled, FISH will prompt participants who exceed a configurable time limit,
        giving them the option to continue or leave. If they exceed the limit too many times,
        they are automatically removed from the session.
    h4 Settings
    dl
        dt Read rules timeout (min)
        dd.
            How many minutes a participant may spend reading the rules before being prompted.
            Set to 0 to disable this timeout.
        dt Lobby wait timeout (min)
        dd.
            How many minutes a participant may wait in the lobby (after reading the rules)
            before being prompted. Set to 0 to disable this timeout.
        dt Prompt timeout (sec)
        dd.
            How many seconds a participant has to respond to an abort prompt before FISH
            acts automatically (proceeding with the default action). Also controls how long
            the session-over and force-abort dialogs wait before redirecting.
        dt Max timeouts
        dd.
            How many times a participant may be prompted before the next timeout results
            in an immediate forced exit, without a prompt.
        dt Abort URL
        dd.
            The URL to redirect to when a participant is aborted (either voluntarily or forced).
            Leave blank to simply end the session without redirecting. Supports the same
            variable substitution as the Redirection URL.
    h4 Prompts
    p.
        When a timeout occurs, the participant sees a modal dialog with options appropriate
        to their current stage:
    dl
        dt While reading rules
        dd Keep Reading, Proceed to Lobby, or Abort
        dt While waiting in the lobby
        dd Keep Waiting or Abort
    p.
        If the participant does not respond within the Prompt timeout, FISH takes the default
        action automatically (counting as one timeout).
    p.
        Once a participant reaches the Max timeouts limit, the next timeout results in an
        immediate forced exit with a notification dialog but no choice of action.
